title: For Sale:  watch out for these scams
postcontent: As if wading thru piles of overpriced glocks and bubba built ARs, low balling asshole pawn star wannabes, wasn't bad enough now the scammers are hitting the list hard. Theres a 1911 listed, a 1960 AK, just for a couple examples. They're pretty easy to spot. There's very little info in the ads and they rarely mention what the gun being sold actually is and say contact x email address for more info. They also don't list a city in the location, just Kentucky Kentucky. I even received two emails today about a rifle I sold and removed my ad for months ago. Both worded the same but with different email addresses. Seems like armslist is starting to cater to these ass monkeys. How else would they get the info for an ad thats been deactivated for months? Thank I'll be moving on to other venues until armslist can pull their heads out of their asses and start catering to the people that made the site so popular in the first place. But anyway just wanted to give those less informed a heads up about this latest round of scams.
